04485nam a22007455i 9780691190396DE-B159720190523123322.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||190523s2018    nju    fo  d z      eng d  a97806911903967 a10.1515/97806911903962doi  a(DE-B1597)501957  a(OCoLC)1076462378  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ 4aBM538.P3bH67 2006eb 7aREL0400102bisacsh 7aREL0400302bisacsh04a296.3/6972231 aHorowitz, Elliott, eauthor.10aReckless Rites :bPurim and the Legacy of Jewish Violence /cElliott Horowitz. 1aPrinceton, NJ : bPrinceton University Press, c[2018] 4cÂ©2006  a1 online resource   atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aJews, Christians, and Muslims from the Ancient to the Modern World00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIllustrations -- tAcknowledgments -- tIntroduction -- tPART ONE.BIBLICAL LEGACIES -- t1. The Book of Esther -- t2. A Pair of Queens -- t3. Mordecai's Reckless Refusal -- t4. The Eternal Haman -- t5.Amalek -- tPART TWO. JEWS LIVING DANGEROUSLY -- t6. "The Fascination of the Abomination" -- t7. Mild Men or Wild Men? -- t8. Ancient Jewish Violence and Modern Scholarship -- t9. Purim, Carnival, and Violence -- t10. Local Purims and the Invention of Tradition -- tAbbreviations -- tBibliography -- tIndex  aHistorical accounts of Jewish violence--particularly against Christians--have long been explosive material. Some historians have distorted these records for anti-Semitic purposes. Others have discounted, dismissed, or simply ignored the evidence, often for apologetic purposes. In Reckless Rites, Elliott Horowitz takes a new and forthright look at both the history of Jewish violence since late antiquity and the ways in which generations of historians have grappled with that history. In the process, he has written the most wide-ranging book on Jewish violence in any language, and the first to fully acknowledge and address the actual anti-Christian practices that became part of the playful, theatrical violence of the Jewish festival of Purim. He has also examined the different ways in which the book of Esther, upon which the festival is based, was used by Jews and Christians over the centuries--whether as an ancient mirror of modern tribulations or as the scriptural basis for anti-Semitic claims regarding the bloodthirstiness of the Jews. Reckless Rites reassesses the historical interpretation of Jewish violence--from the alleged massacre of thousands of Christians in seventh-century Jerusalem to later medieval attacks on Christian symbols such as the crucifix, transgressions that were often committed in full knowledge that their likely consequence would be death. A book that calls for major changes in the way that Jewish history is written and conceptualized, Reckless Rites will be essential reading for scholars and students of history, religion, and Jewish-Christian relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 0aChristianity and other religionsxJudaism. 0aJudaismxRelationsxChristianity. 0aPurim. 0aViolencexReligious aspectsxJudaismxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691190396zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691190396.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN